dult, open 09:00–18:00. The most reliable rainy-day pick, especially for families."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Terminal 21 Pattaya", "description": "Themed city-floor mall at North Pattaya with a cinema and the Pier 21 food court (dishes ฿40–80). Free to enter, open until ~23:00. Easy to fill 2–3 hours."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Central Festival Pattaya", "description": "Bigger beachfront mall in Central Pattaya with international brands, a cinema and sea views. Free to wander, open until ~23:00. Watch the rain roll through while you eat."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "Thai or oil massage", "description": "A 2-hour spa package at Let's Relax (฿1,000–1,200) or Health Land (฿650–700), or a one-hour street massage for ฿250–350. The ideal rainy-day reset for couples."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 5, "name": "Art in Paradise", "description": "Indoor 3D trick-art museum on Second Road, about ฿400 adult, open 09:00–22:00. An hour of interactive photo fun, great with kids and groups."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 6, "name": "Indoor adventure (Bounce, bowling, arcades)", "description": "Trampoline parks (฿450–650/hr), mall bowling alleys (฿80–120/game) and arcades. Air-conditioned energy-burners clustered inside the malls."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 7, "name": "Indoor Muay Thai class", "description": "A drop-in beginner class at Fairtex or a Soi Buakhao camp, ฿300–500 for 1.5–2 hours with gear rental. The best fun-per-baht and a real Thai experience."}]}, {"@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": [{"@type": "Question", "name": "What is there to do in Pattaya when it rains?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Plenty. The most reliable indoor options are Underwater World aquarium (about ฿500), the Terminal 21 and Central Festival malls (free to enter, with cinemas and food courts), a long Thai or oil massage (฿300–1,200), the Art in Paradise 3D museum (฿400), and an indoor Muay Thai class (฿300–500). Most are within a 10–15 minute ride of central Pattaya."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Does it rain all day in Pattaya?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Rarely. In Pattaya's green season, roughly May to October, the typical pattern is a bright morning, a heavy one-to-two-hour downpour in the early afternoon, then clearing skies by evening. True all-day washouts happen but are the exception, so one good indoor anchor activity usually saves the day rather than the whole trip being lost."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "What can you do in Pattaya with kids when it's raining?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Underwater World aquarium is the top family pick at around ฿500 adult and ฿300 child, fully indoor with a walk-through tunnel. Add the Art in Paradise 3D museum (฿400), a trampoline park or arcade inside the malls (฿450–650 per hour), or a cinema and food-court lunch at Terminal 21. All keep kids happy and dry for a couple of hours."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "How much do rainy day activities in Pattaya cost?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "They're cheap. An aquarium or 3D-museum ticket is ฿400–500, a two-hour spa package ฿700–1,200, a mall day with food and a film around ฿250–500, and a Muay Thai drop-in ฿300–500. A typical rainy half-day of one attraction plus a meal and a massage comes to roughly ฿900–1,200 per person."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Are the malls in Pattaya free to enter?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. Both Terminal 21 Pattaya and Central Festival are free to walk into and browse, open until around 22:00–23:00. You only pay for what you buy — a food-court meal is ฿40–80, a cinema ticket about ฿180–260, and a bowling game ฿80–120. They're the city's go-to free shelter when rain hits."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Is it worth visiting Pattaya in the rainy season?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "For many travellers, yes. Green-season rain usually falls in short afternoon bursts, hotels and flights are cheaper, and crowds are thinner. You just need an indoor plan for the wet hours and to keep boat trips flexible. See our full guide on visiting Pattaya in the rainy season for the month-by-month picture."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Can you still go to Koh Larn when it rains?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "You can, but check the forecast first. On a heavy-rain or windy day the sea gets rough, visibility for snorkelling drops, and ferries occasionally pause. If rain is likely, save Koh Larn for a clear morning and use the indoor list instead — refunds on boat trips are rare once you've sailed."}}]}]$b$);
