</header>
<!-- HERO -->
<figure class="art-hero"><img alt="Pattaya beach sunset drone – 10 bestromanticthings to do in Pattaya for couples" fetchpriority="high" height="506" loading="eager" src="../Pattaya-Tum-Gorseller-Resized/pattaya-beach-sunset-drone.webp" width="1100"/>
      <figcaption class="cap"><span class="lead"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-16"><use href="#pg-pin"></use></svg> Romantic Pattaya · sunset on Pratumnak, dinner with a view and quiet Wong Amat beaches</span><span class="credit">Go To Pattaya</span></figcaption></figure>
<!-- TL;DR -->
<div class="tldr">
<h4><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-20"><use href="#pg-info"></use></svg> If you only have 30 seconds</h4>
<p>The most reliably romantic things to do in Pattaya are a <b>sunset on Pratumnak Hill or Wong Amat</b> (free, around <b>6:20pm</b>), a <b>cliff-top or beachfront dinner</b> (mains <b>฿400–900</b>), a <b>couples Thai-oil massage</b> (about <b>฿600–1,200 for two hours</b>), and a quiet <b>Koh Larn day trip</b> (฿30 ferry). Skip Central Pattaya's noisy core and base yourselves around <b>Pratumnak, Jomtien or Naklua</b> — the city's romance lives at its calmer edges, not in the middle of the bar zone.</p>
</div>
</div>
<!-- LAYOUT -->
<div class="art-layout">
<article class="art-body">
<!-- MOBILE STICKY TOC -->
<div class="mtoc">
<details id="mtocDetails">
<summary>
<span class="lbl"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-16"><use href="#pg-menu"></use></svg> Table of contents</span>
