<h1>The 15 best <em>rooftop bars in Pattaya</em> for sunset</h1>
<p class="sub">Pattaya does sunset better than almost anywhere on the Gulf, and the view changes completely depending on which rooftop you pick. These are the best rooftop bars in Pattaya for sunset drinks, ranked by view, vibe and what you actually pay — by an editor who drinks here.</p>
<div class="author-strip">
<div class="av">OV</div>
<div class="who">
<b>Olga Vavilova</b>
<span>Senior writer · 7 years drinking on Pattaya's rooftops</span>
</div>
<div class="as-meta">
<span class="when">
<svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-16 is-muted"><use href="#pg-clock"></use></svg>
            Updated Jun 10, 2026
          </span>
<div class="share-btns">
<button aria-label="Share this article" type="button"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-16"><use href="#pg-share"></use></svg></button>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</header>
<!-- HERO -->
<figure class="art-hero"><img alt="Pattaya beach sunset drone – The 15 bestrooftop bars in Pattayafor sunset" fetchpriority="high" height="506" loading="eager" src="../Pattaya-Tum-Gorseller-Resized/pattaya-beach-sunset-drone.webp" width="1100"/>
      <figcaption class="cap"><span class="lead"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-16"><use href="#pg-pin"></use></svg> Sunset over the Gulf · Pattaya's best rooftop bars, ranked by view and vibe</span><span class="credit">Go To Pattaya</span></figcaption></figure>
<!-- TL;DR -->
<div class="tldr">
<h4><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-20"><use href="#pg-info"></use></svg> If you only have 30 seconds</h4>
<p>For the best all-round sunset, head to <b>Horizon at Hilton Pattaya</b> (Beach Road, 34th floor) — the cleanest Gulf-and-bay view in the city, with cocktails around <b>฿380–520</b>. For something cheaper and more local, <b>Sky Gallery on Pratumnak</b> stacks tables down a cliff straight over the water (mains <b>฿250–600</b>, no cover). For a party with the view, <b>The Sky Pattaya</b> on Walking Street's edge is the late-night pick. Arrive by <b>5:15pm</b> in cool season to get a rail seat before sunset around <b>6:25pm</b>.</p>
</div>
</div>
<!-- LAYOUT -->
<div class="art-layout">
<article class="art-body">
<!-- MOBILE STICKY TOC -->
<div class="mtoc">
<details id="mtocDetails">
<summary>
<span class="lbl"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-16"><use href="#pg-menu"></use></svg> Table of contents</span>
<span class="cur" id="mtocCur">How we picked</span>
</summary>
<ol id="mtocList">
<li><a href="#how-we-picked">How we picked</a></li>
<li><a href="#top-picks">Our top 3 for sunset</a></li>
<li><a href="#the-list">The 15 best rooftop bars</a></li>
<li><a href="#prices">What a rooftop night costs</a></li>
<li><a href="#by-area">Best rooftops by area</a></li>
<li><a href="#timing">When to go for the best sunset</a></li>
<li><a href="#avoid">What to watch out for</a></li>
<li><a href="#faq">FAQ</a></li>
</ol>
</details>
<div class="mtoc-bar"><i id="mtocBar"></i></div>
</div>
<p>Pattaya gets an unfair reputation, but on one thing there's no argument: the sunset is genuinely world-class. Because the city faces west across the Gulf of Thailand, the sun drops straight into the sea most of the year, and the curve of the bay means almost every high rooftop gets a clean, uninterrupted view of it. After seven years living here and far too many golden-hour drinks "for research," these are the rooftop bars I actually send friends to.</p>
<p>This is a ranked, honest list of the <strong>best rooftop bars in Pattaya for sunset</strong> — what the view is really like, the vibe, what you'll pay in 2026 Thai baht, and which ones are worth the trip versus which are coasting on a nice photo. If you want the wider nightlife picture, pair this with our <a class="inline" href="pillar-eat-drinks.html">eat &amp; drink guide</a>.</p>
<h2 id="how-we-picked">How we picked</h2>
<figure class="art-img">
<img alt="Pattaya walking street 2 in Pattaya, Thailand" height="428" loading="lazy" src="../Pattaya-Tum-Gorseller-Resized/pattaya-walking-street-2.webp" width="760"/>
<figcaption>Pattaya Walking Street 2 · The 15 bestrooftop bars in Pattayafor sunset</figcaption>
</figure>

<p>I drink on these rooftops — repeatedly, as a paying customer, never on a comped invite. Every venue here was visited at golden hour within the last year, and I went back to the top picks more than once to check whether a good night was a fluke. Ranking weighed four things: the actual <strong>sunset view</strong> (how clean, how high, how much sky and sea), the <strong>vibe</strong> (relaxed, romantic or party), <strong>value</strong> (does the drink price match the experience), and <strong>practicality</strong> (can you get a seat, is the music bearable, is the staff friendly).</p>
<p>I deliberately mixed price tiers. Some of Pattaya's best sunset spots are luxury hotel sky bars on Beach Road; others are scruffy, brilliant cliff-edge restaurants on Pratumnak Hill where a Chang costs a fraction of the hotel price and the view is arguably better. Both belong on a real list.</p>
<div class="callout">
<div class="ic"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-20"><use href="#pg-verified"></use></svg></div>
<div><h4>No pay-to-play</h4><p>Nobody pays to appear on this list. Every rooftop was visited and paid for at full price, and prices below were checked at the bar in 2026 — the same standard we hold across every <a class="inline" href="plan-my-trip.html">trip-planning guide</a>. If a famous name isn't here, it's because the view or the value didn't earn it.</p></div>
</div>
<h2 id="top-picks">Our top 3 for sunset</h2>
<p>If you only have one or two evenings, start here. These three cover the three reasons people go up: the cleanest view, the best value with a sea view, and the best party-with-a-view.</p>
<div class="verdict">
<div class="qv">
<div class="qv-label"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-16"><use href="#pg-sunset"></use></svg> Best view overall</div>
<div class="qv-name">Horizon · Hilton</div>
<div class="qv-detail">34th floor, Beach Road · cocktails ฿380–520</div>
</div>
<div class="qv">
<div class="qv-label"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-16"><use href="#pg-sea-view"></use></svg> Best value sea view</div>
<div class="qv-name">Sky Gallery</div>
<div class="qv-detail">Pratumnak cliff · mains ฿250–600 · no cover</div>
</div>
<div class="qv">
<div class="qv-label"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-16"><use href="#pg-nightlife"></use></svg> Best party rooftop</div>
<div class="qv-name">The Sky Pattaya</div>
<div class="qv-detail">Near Walking Street · DJ nights · open late</div>
</div>
</div>
<h2 id="the-list">The 15 best rooftop bars in Pattaya</h2>
<figure class="art-img">
<img alt="Pattaya city sign in Pattaya, Thailand" height="428" loading="lazy" src="../Pattaya-Tum-Gorseller-Resized/pattaya-city-sign.webp" width="760"/>
<figcaption>Pattaya City Sign – explore Pattaya's best spots</figcaption>
</figure>

<p>Ranked top to bottom on the balance of view, vibe and value. Heights are approximate, prices are 2026 bar prices, and "sunset side" tells you whether the view actually faces west over the Gulf.</p>
<h3>1. Horizon Rooftop Bar — Hilton Pattaya (Central)</h3>
<p>The benchmark. On the <strong>34th floor</strong> above Central Festival on Beach Road, Horizon has the highest clean sea view in central Pattaya, looking straight down the bay to Koh Larn. Cocktails run <strong>฿380–520</strong> and there's no entry fee, though it gets busy — arrive by 5:15pm in cool season for a rail seat. Smart-casual; flip-flops are fine but vest tops get the side-eye.</p>
<h3>2. Sky Gallery — Pratumnak Hill</h3>
<p>My personal favourite for value. It's not a tower — it's an open-air restaurant terraced down a cliff right above the water on Pratumnak, so the Gulf fills your whole view at eye level. Mains are <strong>฿250–600</strong>, beers from <strong>฿120</strong>, and there's no cover. Book a front table for sunset; walk-ins land on the upper deck.</p>
<h3>3. The Sky Pattaya — near Walking Street (South)</h3>
<p>The party pick. A glass-walled rooftop on the South Pattaya side near Walking Street, with DJ sets later on and a young, loud crowd. Cocktails <strong>฿250–390</strong>, beers around <strong>฿140</strong>. Come for sunset, stay for the energy, then drop straight into <a class="inline" href="blog-walking-street-guide.html">Walking Street</a> a few minutes away.</p>
<h3>4. Drift Bar — Avani Pattaya Resort (Central)</h3>
<p>A poolside-meets-rooftop bar with a tidy, low-key Beach Road sunset. Less dramatic than Horizon but more relaxed and rarely crowded. Cocktails <strong>฿320–450</strong>. Good for a quiet couple's drink rather than a scene.</p>
<h3>5. Rimpa Lapin — Pratumnak Hill</h3>
<p>A Pattaya institution. A huge open-air clifftop restaurant on Pratumnak with one of the most romantic sunset settings in the city — tiered tables, the sea below, the lights of the bay coming on. It's a restaurant first (mains <strong>฿200–650</strong>), so book ahead for a front-row table at golden hour.</p>
<h3>6. The Roof Sky Bar — Siam@Siam (Central)</h3>
<p>Around the 24th floor of the Siam@Siam design hotel, with a sleek, design-led feel and a solid city-and-sea view. Cocktails <strong>฿300–420</strong>. A good middle option between hotel polish and the cliff bars.</p>
<h3>7. Skylette Lounge — Wong Amat / Naklua</h3>
<p>Up in the quieter north end above Wong Amat Beach, this lounge gives you the Naklua coastline and a calmer, more grown-up crowd than the centre. Cocktails <strong>฿340–480</strong>. Worth it if you're staying north and don't want the Beach Road crush.</p>
<h3>8. Edge Rooftop — Hilton Pattaya (Central)</h3>
<p>Horizon's slightly lower sibling lounge in the same hotel, with the same bay view from a comfortable seated setting. Pricing sits with Horizon at <strong>฿380–520</strong> for cocktails. Pick this if Horizon's rail is full.</p>
<h3>9. Sky Beach — Central Beach Road</h3>
<p>A breezy, mid-height beach-road rooftop that's more about an easy sundowner than a knockout view. Beers from <strong>฿130</strong>, cocktails <strong>฿260–360</strong>. Reliable, unfussy, central.</p>
<h3>10. Pinnacle Lounge — Jomtien</h3>
<p>One of the better high options in <a class="inline" href="blog-jomtien-vs-central-pattaya.html">Jomtien</a>, looking back along the long Jomtien beachfront. Quieter and cheaper than the centre, with cocktails around <strong>฿280–400</strong>. Great if you're based south.</p>
<h3>11. Mata Bar — Pratumnak</h3>
<p>A smaller, more intimate rooftop near the Pratumnak viewpoint area, popular for sunset photos. Beers from <strong>฿110</strong>, simple cocktails <strong>฿200–320</strong>. Limited seats, so come early.</p>
<h3>12. Cape Dara Rooftop — Naklua</h3>
<p>The rooftop at the Cape Dara Resort on the northern headland, with a wide sweep across Naklua and Wong Amat. Smarter, resort-priced (cocktails <strong>฿350–500</strong>) and pleasantly quiet on weeknights.</p>
<h3>13. The Bay Rooftop — Central</h3>
<p>A dependable central rooftop bar good for groups and after-work drinks rather than a romantic sunset. Beers from <strong>฿120</strong>, cocktails <strong>฿250–360</strong>. View is fine, not spectacular.</p>
<h3>14. Sundown Social — South Pattaya</h3>
<p>A casual lower rooftop with a friendly, mixed crowd and a partial sea view through the buildings. Cheap and cheerful — beers from <strong>฿100</strong>, cocktails <strong>฿200–300</strong>. More about the hang than the horizon.</p>
<h3>15. Vue Rooftop — Jomtien</h3>
<p>A small Jomtien-side rooftop that rounds out the list for southern stays. Modest view, relaxed vibe, cocktails around <strong>฿240–340</strong>. Worth knowing about if you're nearby, not worth a special trip across town.</p>
<h2 id="prices">What a rooftop night costs</h2>
<p>Pattaya rooftops span a wide price range, and the gap is real: a hotel sky bar will cost roughly double a Pratumnak cliff restaurant for the same two drinks. Here's what to budget per person for sunset and a couple of rounds, in 2026 baht.</p>
<div class="money-grid">
<div class="money-card"><div class="label">Hotel sky bar / 2 drinks</div><div class="val">฿700–1,100</div><p>Horizon, Edge, Cape Dara. Polished, highest views, no cover but premium drinks.</p></div>
<div class="money-card"><div class="label">Cliff restaurant / 2 drinks + a bite</div><div class="val">฿500–900</div><p>Sky Gallery, Rimpa Lapin. Best value sea view; you're paying for food too.</p></div>
<div class="money-card"><div class="label">Party rooftop / 2 drinks</div><div class="val">฿500–800</div><p>The Sky Pattaya. DJ nights, louder, occasional minimum-spend on big events.</p></div>
<div class="money-card"><div class="label">Casual / local rooftop</div><div class="val">฿300–550</div><p>Mata, Sundown Social, Jomtien spots. Beers from ฿100–130, simpler cocktails.</p></div>
</div>
