, "name": "The Bay Rooftop (Central)", "description": "Dependable group-friendly central rooftop. Beers from ฿120, cocktails ฿250–360."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 14, "name": "Sundown Social (South)", "description": "Casual lower rooftop with a partial sea view and a friendly crowd. Beers from ฿100."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 15, "name": "Vue Rooftop (Jomtien)", "description": "Small relaxed Jomtien-side rooftop. Cocktails ฿240–340. Handy for southern stays."}]}, {"@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": [{"@type": "Question", "name": "What is the best rooftop bar in Pattaya for sunset?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "For the best overall sunset, Horizon Rooftop Bar on the 34th floor of the Hilton Pattaya wins on view — the highest, cleanest look down the bay toward Koh Larn, with cocktails around ฿380–520 and no entry fee. For the best value sea view, the Pratumnak cliff restaurant Sky Gallery is hard to beat, with the Gulf at eye level and mains from ฿250."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "How much do rooftop bar drinks cost in Pattaya?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "It depends on the tier. Hotel sky bars like Horizon and Cape Dara charge ฿380–520 for cocktails, while Pratumnak cliff bars and casual rooftops run ฿200–390, with local beers from ฿100–140. Budget roughly ฿700–1,100 per person for two drinks at a hotel rooftop, or ฿300–550 at a casual spot."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Do Pattaya rooftop bars charge an entry fee?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Most of the best rooftop bars in Pattaya have no cover charge — including Horizon, Sky Gallery and Rimpa Lapin. Some party rooftops add a minimum spend on DJ or event nights rather than a flat fee. Always check for a service charge plus VAT (around 10% + 7%) on your final bill at hotel sky bars."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "What time is sunset in Pattaya?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Sunset in Pattaya falls roughly between 6:15pm and 6:35pm year-round, a little earlier in December and later in June. Because the city faces west over the Gulf, the sun drops straight into the sea. Aim to be seated by 5:15–5:30pm to get a west-facing rail table, especially on weekends."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Which Pattaya area has the best rooftop bars?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Central Beach Road has the highest hotel sky bars (Horizon, Drift, Sky Beach), while Pratumnak Hill has the best-value cliff-edge bars with the sea at eye level (Sky Gallery, Rimpa Lapin). Naklua and Wong Amat are quieter and more grown-up, and Jomtien is cheaper and more relaxed. Choose by where you're staying."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Are rooftop bars in Pattaya good for couples?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. The Pratumnak cliff restaurants Rimpa Lapin and Sky Gallery are the most romantic, with tiered tables right over the water at golden hour. For a polished couple's drink, Drift at Avani or the Cape Dara rooftop in Naklua are quieter than the central towers. Book a front table ahead for sunset."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Do I need to book a Pattaya rooftop bar in advance?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "For sunset on weekends, yes — especially at the cliff restaurants where front tables go fast. Sky Gallery and Rimpa Lapin are best booked a day or two ahead for a rail seat. Hotel sky bars like Horizon are usually walk-in, but arriving by 5:15pm makes a big difference to getting the best view."}}]}]$b$);
