<!-- TL;DR -->
<div class="tldr">
<h4><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-20"><use href="#pg-info"></use></svg> If you only have 30 seconds</h4>
<p><b>Choose the Sanctuary of Truth</b> if you want one jaw-dropping, photogenic monument you can see in <b>1.5–2 hours</b> close to town (about <b>฿500</b>, in Naklua). <b>Choose Nong Nooch</b> if you want a half-to-full day with kids — gardens, an <b>elephant show</b> and a cultural show across a huge park (about <b>฿700–800</b>, but <b>40 minutes south</b> of the city). If you only have time for one and you're chasing the iconic Pattaya photo, the Sanctuary wins; if you're travelling with children or want more bang per ticket, Nong Nooch wins.</p>
</div>
</div>
