<span class="dot"></span><span class="s"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-16 is-muted"><use href="#pg-pin"></use></svg> Naklua</span>
</div>
<p>You won't find this in most tourist guides because the vendors don't advertise and the menus are entirely in Thai. It's the night market that grew up around the working fishing pier where boats come back at sundown. Walk past the boats, choose your fish (it might still be moving), and the vendor grills or fries it at the next stall over. <em>Goong pao</em> here is ฿120 — about a fifth of a Beach Road price. Bring a Thai friend or Google Translate's camera, and go hungry.</p>
<dl class="mini-spec">
<div class="pair"><dt><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-16"><use href="#pg-price"></use></svg> Per person</dt><dd>฿80–300 / dish</dd></div>
