<p>Sang Som (no relation to the rum) is where Thai TV food shows have filmed for the past decade. Still affordable, still genuinely good — just no longer secret. The signature is <em>pu pad pong karee</em>: blue crab tossed in yellow curry and egg, the version other restaurants in town are trying to imitate. The dining room is open-air and fan-cooled, the tables turn fast. Best for groups of four-plus, because the dishes are big and meant to share.</p>
